## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests reviewed — 0 contain meaningful assertions.** This is a textbook **coverage-touching** suite: every public method on `ProductCatalog` is invoked to satisfy coverage metrics, but no test verifies observable behavior. A bug in any method would pass the entire suite.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 3 (systemic — affecting all 10 tests) |
| Medium   | 2 |

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (systemic — all 10 tests)

Every public method is methodically called with no verification of outcomes. The suite exists to make a coverage report green, not to catch regressions. This single pattern explains why bugs escape to production at 95% coverage.

#### 2. No Assertions (6 of 10 tests)

These tests execute code and silently succeed regardless of what happens:

| Test method | Line | What goes unverified |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17–21 | Product was actually persisted |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 31–36 | Price was actually changed (a no-op `UpdatePrice` passes) |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 38–43 | Product was actually removed (a no-op `RemoveProduct` passes) |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 62–66 | Count is correct (could return -1 and pass) |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 68–74 | Prices were actually discounted |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 84–88 | Products were actually imported |

**Fix — `UpdatePrice_Works` (representative example):**

```csharp
// BEFORE — no assertion, UpdatePrice could be a no-op
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
}

// AFTER — verifies the observable outcome
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ExistingProduct_PriceIsUpdated()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}
```

**Fix — `RemoveProduct_Works`:**

```csharp
// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_ExistingProduct_ProductIsNoLongerFound()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}
```

**Fix — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works`:**

```csharp
// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_TenPercent_ReducesAllPrices()
{
